    "properties_description": "The main therapeutic properties of Podalyria parvifolia are its anti-inflammatory, antioxidant, antimicrobial, antidiabetic, and antiviral activities. The anti-inflammatory properties of the plant are attributed to the presence of flavonoids and saponins, which have been shown to inhibit the production of pro-inflammatory enzymes and cytokines. Antioxidant activity is also present, due to the plant's content of phenolic compounds and flavonoids, which scavenge free radicals and protect against oxidative stress. The antimicrobial properties of Podalyria parvifolia are attributed to its volatile oils, which have been shown to inhibit the growth of various bacteria and fungi, making it a potential natural remedy for wound infections. The antidiabetic and antiviral properties of the plant are also noteworthy, with studies suggesting that its bioactive compounds may help to regulate blood sugar levels and inhibit the replication of certain viruses.",
