    "preparations_description": "The main herbal preparations of Podalyria parvifolia are infusion, tincture, tea, salve and decoction. Infusion and decoction are aqueous preparations used for their anthelmintic and antiseptic properties, particularly for treating gastrointestinal issues and wounds. Tea is an infusion used for its antipyretic and anti-inflammatory effects, mainly for fever reduction and pain relief. Tincture is a concentrated liquid used for its anthelmintic properties to treat parasitic infections, and salve is a topical preparation used to treat skin conditions and wounds due to its antiseptic and anti-inflammatory properties. These preparations are made from the plant's leaves and pods, which contain flavonoids, alkaloids, and saponins responsible for their medicinal properties.",
